Text.val: -- In case of CV or mobiles only allowed clients have to be selected (defined in table CFLC), the where clause
is used in submodules where 'normal' XPA data selection is used
-- Populate table with deductions/credit and margin amounts
... in admin currency (not relevant fro VC/Mobiles)

ExpSyntax.val: 'exists(select * from '&Trim({32768,9})&'/CFLC where CFLC_ADMNO='&Trim(Str({1,10},'4'))&' and CFLC_CLNTNO='&Trim(Str({1,11},'5'))&' and CFLC_USRID='&''''&Trim({1,7})&''''&' and CFLC_ADMNOALLOWED = CLNT101_ADMNO and CFLC_CLNTNOALLOWED = CLNT102_CLNTNO'&')'

Text.val: .. Collect commercially connected clients (only for Windows client sessions)

SQL_STMT_U.val: select CMCD_MARKCODE, min(CODE_DESCRIPTION), cast(sum(CMCD_SPECIALACCOUNTC + CMCD_DISPUTESGROSSC) as decimal (13,2)), cast(sum(CMCD_SPECIALACCOUNTH + CMCD_DISPUTESGROSSH) as decimal (13,2)) from :1/CMCD left outer join :1/CODE on CODE_TYPE=51 and CODE_LANGUAGE=':4' and CODE_NUMBERN=CMCD_MARKCODE where CMCD_ADMNO=:2 and CMCD_CLNTNO= :3 and (CMCD_SPECIALACCOUNTC<>0 or CMCD_DISPUTESGROSSC<>0 or CMCD_SPECIALACCOUNTH<>0 or CMCD_DISPUTESGROSSH<>0) group by CMCD_MARKCODE for fetch only
